Group.name: CanSat
Group.description: CanSat: Educational project where students design, build, and launch a small satellite housed in a soda-can-sized container. Typically used in STEM programs, CanSats provide hands-on experience in satellite development, telemetry, and data analysis. Aiming to inspire future engineers and scientists, CanSats offer a practical introduction to the principles of aerospace engineering.
